## Post 2

**Date:** 3 July 2026

**Topic:** The skills school doesn't teach

### Summary
Justin argues that traditional education prepares people for outdated systems by rewarding memorization and rule-following. In contrast, success in the real world depends on relationship-building, communication, adaptability, and creating value. He introduces seven practical skills he believes are essential for entrepreneurship but are rarely taught in formal education.

### Main Takeaway
Professional success depends more on interpersonal skills, adaptability, and initiative than academic achievement alone.

