## Post 3

**Date:** 2 July 2026

**Topic:** Entrepreneurship is the real safety net

### Summary
Justin reflects on spending years trying to remain employable before realizing that entrepreneurial skills provide greater long-term security. He argues that building businesses develops creativity, problem-solving, marketing, and execution skills that employers value while also creating independent income opportunities.

### Main Takeaway
Building entrepreneurial skills reduces career risk by creating the ability to generate opportunities independently instead of relying solely on traditional employment.

