## Post 4

**Date:** 1 July 2026

**Topic:** Action beats intelligence

### Summary
Justin emphasizes that taking action consistently outperforms endless planning and research. He explains that many intelligent people delay execution while trying to fully understand every detail, whereas those who start imperfectly gain real-world experience much faster. He advocates learning through experimentation rather than waiting for perfect knowledge.

### Main Takeaway
Execution accelerates learning. Real progress comes from taking action, making mistakes, and improving through experience.

