## Post 5

**Date:** 30 June 2026

**Topic:** Confidence comes before evidence

### Summary
Justin shares how believing in himself before having proof enabled him to achieve major career milestones, from leading revenue at a growing company to building a one-person business exceeding $15 million. He explains that successful entrepreneurs often act on belief before external validation exists and gradually grow into that confidence through consistent action.

### Main Takeaway
Meaningful achievements begin with believing in your potential before results appear. Confidence should drive action rather than depend on prior success.

